  "body": "lajha: 0.9.0\r\n\r\n### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nDuring shutdown, got:\r\n```\r\n WARNING  12-07 15:41:19              FullNode  Task <coroutine object Node.handle_network_id_requests at 0x7f1f44bf87d8> finished unexpectedly:\r\n   DEBUG  12-07 15:41:19              FullNode  Task failure traceback\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/home/jcarver/code/py-evm/p2p/service.py\", line 141, in _run_task_wrapper\r\n    await awaitable\r\n  File \"/home/jcarver/code/py-evm/p2p/service.py\", line 160, in _run_daemon_task_wrapper\r\n    await awaitable\r\n  File \"/home/jcarver/code/py-evm/trinity/nodes/base.py\", line 60, in handle_network_id_requests\r\n    async for req in self.event_bus.stream(NetworkIdRequest):\r\n  File \"/home/jcarver/code/py-evm/venv/lib/python3.6/site-packages/lahja/endpoint.py\", line 267, in stream\r\n    raise e\r\n  File \"/home/jcarver/code/py-evm/venv/lib/python3.6/site-packages/lahja/endpoint.py\", line 261, in stream\r\n    yield await queue.get()\r\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.6/asyncio/queues.py\", line 167, in get\r\n    yield from getter\r\nconcurrent.futures._base.CancelledError\r\n```\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nMaybe use the new `self.wait_iter` so the iteration dies when the service is cancelled.",
